      "text": "In this book, the conditions under which wars occur are analyzed from a systems theory perspective. The author incorporates biological and psychoanalytical models as well as sociological insights. The result is that such battles are generally not fought for the sake of any economic or libidinal interests, but are fought over seemingly antiquated values such as [[honor]], [[pride]], and [[status]]. In the author's view, wars are therefore to be understood as a continuation of sport by other means and, not to be neglected, as the ultimate form of entertainment – at least for the observers not directly involved."
